<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 04 at 3:44PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Newton,
southwestern Kemper, southeastern Neshoba and northwestern Lauderdale
Counties through 430 PM CDT...
At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Damascus, or 15 miles west of Meridian Station, moving southeast at
15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Martin around 400 PM CDT.
Prismatic around 410 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
